kinhou06/09/24
||27th November, 1983: After the destruction ensued by the Astralis-Luna War, the Stellar Empire, who valiantly fought agains the traitor Maritopia and Luna, was able to defeat both at a great cost. However there is a silver lining...

* 98% of the population in Emerina proper had died, from a population of 240 million, that means that the remaining Karemian population in the ground is around 4,800,000.

* Foundation was destroyed during the war, as were all our space stations... however. New Emerald and New Ruby live.

* New Emerald has a population of 7,500 people, and New Ruby around 2,300 people.

* The Stellar Empress and Emperor reside in new Emerald, with their family.

* There is no hope in Astralis, this planet is a husk of its former self. We must... go... faster, and leave for New Emerald and New Ruby.

* To achieve this, we must rebuild our launching facility in the West Coast, and regroup into Polnoch.

* Our colonies still have launch capabilities, but they will be kept offline until we have the capabilities to also launch things, this will be necessary for the planetary transfer...

* We will try to learn anything from the downed robots and ships that can help us.||

penguin335506/09/24
Feb 6th, 1984

Most of the nation has been turned to ash but a few still live on, carrying the hope of the deceased who came before them. In the deepest underground complexes and mountain bunkers in Kai Shi, Columbia, and the Dotramese Federation, survivors begin to emerge. These first brave souls begin to take note of what is still available after the glassing. During evacuations, the government decided to prioritize saving the best and brightest, and knowledge from all fields, but mostly focusing on rocketry, nuclear power, history, and culture. As such, while most production facilities have been destroyed, the nation still has the knowledge to carry onwards. Food, as it turns out, is not the biggest issue. The Irminsul Tree survived the glassing. While scarred, it stood proud in the dead land around it. After coming out, the country attempts to communicate with all oversea colonies and assets. While we can no longer hold them, we can try bringing them home with the few air assets we have in the mountain hangers. During this, we find out that while a few base personnel has survived, all assets have been destroyed, including the mysterious purple seed and mutants in the Genetic Laboratory of Filipania. Next we contact all nations we can, from Maritopia to Incahinda to Tsuki Taiyo.

penguin335506/09/24
||We agree to this by using as many surface ships and submarines possible, also bringing a select few cultural objects, history books, and 10 large and preserved fruit samples from the Irminsul Tree. That said, obviously, a lot of non-essential knowledge is left behind. Thus, a decision is formed, to split the government into two for the time being. One, called the Heavenly Kai Shi government, led by the Crown Prince, heads towards Emerina. The other, called the Astralis Government of Kai Shi, is led by aging Da Wei of the former Peoples Republic. The two carry the most powerful and long range communication radios they have and agree to keep in touch. The Astralis government agrees to manage the remnants of the nation, while the Heavenly will head to Emerina, and most likely evacuate beyond the stars to ensure the continuation of the nation if one fails.

January 1st, 1985: After several months, the dust from the Astralis-Luna war, or the Second Solar War has settled. The Provisional Stellar Interplanetary Union has been able to settle in the areas around Polnoch decently, the city had just been constructed around the upgraded METRO system, and the lack of radiation has allowed for the free reactivation of material manufacturing infrastructure and hydrocarbon extraction on the shores. More people from all across the Stellar Empire have arrived, and will keep arriving until all 22 million people reach the shores of the Western Coast. With the West Coast's nuclear reactors back online, we will begin to reactivate production plants for CH4 and LH2 underground and overhead, if any remain standing. Outside of this, Polnoch has seen the most development, the city was incomplete anyways, so at least, we have a good foundation to work with. Putting the other several millions of people arriving from our partners, we will surpass the 30 million people mark. More than enough to run a new beginning, a new nation, from the scratch. Hydroponic complexes have been reactivated and the new areas of the METRO system designed specifically for survival against the volcano (rated for 150~ million people), more will be activated periodically as demand increases.

We begin to program the new software that will be utilized to achieve Plan "REACH", Andromeda Block 2 begins development.

We have instructed everyone to brace for the volcanic eruption. We have prepared adequately, but the sooth may be an issue. We will figure out how to clean it.

May 1st, 1986:

A shimmering spark still remains in what was once Jormund.

Hastily designed bunkers, reinforced basements and heavily modified air-raid shelters hold what remains of Jormund's population. Most newly springing settlements are formed around either monuments or national figures of a by-gone era. Streets are found to have loose bands of survivors, or criminals still plundering the old lands.

Old radio stations would have been modified to become beacons within the nation, turning more as centers of recruitment for the mere ~1,000,000 population that remains. From the few, these hands will help slowly rebuild the ashes of a once helpful nation, one that even when threats loomed over the horizon still leant a helping hand...

From our geothermal powerplants being offline, to the 'million free hands' project being fully incapable of working, the time since our nation's birth have been nothing but kindness. Yet, we're paid in smoke and blood, with threats of violence and now a lasting scar upon our war-torn world. Just living together, huddled in our caves, scavenging the scraps of the old world to build the same monuments we now gather around.

And thus, community by community, we begin to gradually rebuild. Our first focus being the three major things to survive, Food, Water and Shelter. Water would be seen as a major concern, with wells being dug out and tested, to our once old homes remodeled to their concrete foundations. Rebuilding will be long, but we will rebuild once again...

January 7th, 1989:

The ISN Tolvar docks at a makeshift port, and makes do with an expeditionary force to explore the region and find out what's going on. The locals regard us with much respect and deference; indeed we are among the last of the Stellar Empire. Human or otherwise, they do not bother the men from the submarine.

A taste of the true conditions of the land was acquired as soon as we cross into South Karemi's far fringes; the lakes between Rio and Nusia. The expeditionary team was caught in a skirmish between a Lormradamee raider group and Nusian scavengers, fighting over a piece of fallen Lunarian robotics. Somehow, the Lormradamee and the scavengers alike still had bullets to fight with. If it was not that, then it was an array of bow and arrow and war chanting... At one point while hunkered down in the jungle for our own safety, we watched as a Lormradamee hauled out a photon cannon scavenged from the wreckage around it, and proceeded with destroying their advesaries who had found themselves entrenched. The Lormradamee wielded it in posture and manner like we witnessed we the Rikkan robots had during the war. Its eyes wide and expressions unmoving for as long as said weapon was worn on its paws. That is when we knew we had to retreat; but with more questions than answers as to South Karemi's happenings.

January 8th, 1989:

Fifty kilometers out from the skirmish; we marched along on foot, until we had encountered the same column of Lormradamee fighters rolling out from the same area presumably. They were, unlike us, equipped with armored cars and trucks of various standings in degradation and condition. Alas we had hailed them; approaching from the brush from behind, equipped with our naval caps and weapons raised for easy identification. We strike up a chat with the truck leading the convoy, first inquiring about the "massive laser beam" we witnessed back there, which presently was nowhere to be seen. We are given no true answer; but a "PEW PEW!" and a bout of laughter from the entire group. Annoyed, we ask them where their superiors are.. or rather, WHO they were.

We are told to board the truck and ride along, sat right in the middle of an array of furballs and right on top of a strange metal box. These lormradamee were apparently headed right en route to their bosses. We presume we were going southeast wards, someplace to Tarshik .. hours and hours of jungle and wreckage would pass us before we saw the objective of our detour.

We stopped at a small blast door in the mountainous frontier between Tarshik and Rokkan, a gate that was once surrounded by fencing, stone towers, lights and several more gates infront of it now demolished. One-by-one, the Lormradamee disembarked from their vehicles and hoarded to the door, knocking on it and gekkering for whoever may be on the other end to open it. And so, seemingly automatically, did it oblige. Only when the coast seem clear of Lormradamee, yet the door to this facility wide open, did we suddenly feel the box of steel lift up from under where we were told to sit, and did we see that we were being carried inside by around twenty more fox. "HUT! HUT! HUT!"

foxbowl_22106/12/24
We were lead into a room of wires and nearly a ton of computers strewn throughout. To our left corner a couch of green and loose feathers sat, with around four foxes pointing their eyes to a television whose wired connections swam out into the sea of other wires on the floor. On the television played a deteriorated copy of the hit film Sholay on HVS. Behind us, the foxes that came with us dragged the box of steel into the room, and infront of us were a Rokuzawan man and seven heavily armed Incahindan infantrymen. They stood around a desk crowded with disassembled, molten, wrecked components of Rikkan robots, arraigned in an orderly pattern of disassembly. The Rokuzawan man sat at the desk, tools-a-plenty in his hands, not at all paying mind to the new precense.


The Infantrymen, however, immediately marched up to face us, blocking our path forth. Though confrontational, they would first greet us with shared salutes, before their "squad leader" scolded us on our continued precense.


"Sailors, you're supposed to be with the Emerinans in Polnoch! Why do you stay here?"


We ask them the same.


"Listen, listen closely. Things are about to get really bad here. The Lormradamee have been left without a leader, and this land with barely a people. It is only a matter of time before they find out the Empress had abandoned them; and what comes from that will in no way be good."

"The Sun forbid; in the absence of a guiding, divine force, they begin reconciling with their truer, wretched origins.."

The leader of our own crew raises a brow and crosses his arms. He's referring to the old Ancient Origin theory, a mystery yet unsolved since the war; a thesis yet unproven. Apparently to Incahindans it has become more relevant than ever now, though the men present seem to take it as fact.. unnerving.

The cheers of the foxmen as the climax of they film they view in the corner is reached drowns out the contemplative silence that ensues.

Two of the infantrymen trudge past us, headed for the box of steel. We step aside and watch as they attempt to cut it open with a saw on the spot.. maybe with the aid of crowbars and some sledgehammers.

"No. We believe not.. The Lormradamee respond too well with Rikkan tech, some of us think they are Rikkan tech. We can never be so sure, you see? Luna struck from both within our soil and from space. The expedition returns to the submarine. Some of the Incahindan remnant leadership have gone mad, it appears. Distrustful even of the Lormradamee who live alongside them now. A faction of us wants to follow their advice and make way to Polnoch.. another faction, recognizing the issues this may bring for the Stellar realm and faith, and unable to sate their curiosity, advocate to prod deeper.

## Despite Everything | July 1st, 1989

The Interplanetary Milkdromeda System has continued secretive testing, the vehicle is a behemoth larger than the RSFV Andromeda Launch System. 20 meters wide and 170 meters tall with both the booster and actual spaceship, made of new alloys and materials discovered over the years in the now destroyed ISWP, and building upon the success of the somewhat fast reusability that the Andromeda system provided. We have used smaller rockets to test REDACTED. And with the mastery over the G-Fold algorithm, and slightly reversed engineered Lunarian computing technology combined with our own advances, we finally have the power needed to achieve this feat. The actual ship without the booster is nowhere near as large as some of the ships the mighty SASF used to field, however, the fact that such a ship is being built in the surface and not in space is already a show of progress, the ship proper is 70 meters long.

The ship will carry some defense systems, mainly to deal with the debris, utilizing the energy of the ships reactors and LANTRE engines to power strong laser and point defenses. The ship will have a system to spin on its own axis and simulate gravity, a solar sail system and so on. In its cargo version, the ship is able to ferry 300 tons of cargo between celestial bodies.

This will be the ship to bring us back to the stars, despite everything.

foxbowl_22106/14/24
July 2nd, 1990:

# THE GREAT CONSPIRACY

The supervolcano lies dormant still, its time long overdue. With faith in the stellar way of life in various places; some feeling depressed and vengeful about the fall of Astralis, many questioning the legitimacy of the Empress, and the various traditionally sunkterist/montoist features of their lives like the Lormradamee, their origins in the sun, their traditions in their worship.. Why, did after our victory against the ultimate lunar enemy did the Stellar Empress not return? The Sun itself only shines upon us from afar still, indifferent, cold to us even. We feel both blessed in our victory over Luna yet at the same time we are left with desolation; so little salvation to be had. Almost as if we were in purgatory from the eighties onward. It's all perpetually surreal for those who remain.

The events that had developed all nations of the Karemian continent to the point we are now, whether the invasion by Luna was inevitable or not, can all be traced back to the Supervolcano scare. Emerina had used this as justification to conquer and wield their power as they pleased. Wed the Stellar Empress. Seize the stars and build an armada capable of contesting Luna, drag the entire world under its wing and bring resistant empires to heel. In the face of annihilation they pulled through and cemented themselves as the world hegemon in spite of it, the beacon of progress, who which the whole world stood in solidarity with.
foxbowl_22106/14/24
Except it becomes increasingly apparent as the years go by that there were no such risk of annihilation. We are all in our desolation left confused, even unknowing as to whether to consider the events of the past thirty years to be for nought. How did Emerina justify all of this, then? Were they fooled by a cruel trick ofnature? Did they... lie? What twistedly successful grab for power was this? Emerina faced the scorn of the Sun and it must become great and change its ways in the face of death, thus was the ultimate test from God for such a great nation!

So we thought; and the Sun in fact remained indifferent. The Stellar Empire, the world, was crushed by the rage of its polar opposite. What God had planned had manifested not, or had manifested in the worst way possible. The holy origins of many of our creatures have come into question; many think the Lormradamee was a Rikkan innovation all along... and if that were true, what is the Empress, indeed their ultimate form?
foxbowl_22106/14/24
So many questions remain now; but all that is known by is us that, in the lightest possible terms, all that we thought to be true before, may not be. How do we even comprehend our own history in the face of all this?

xzgamer55006/15/24
# The Dawn of a New Era

It was July 10th 1990 and the day was finally here. After years of work everything is finally ready. Below the ruined city of Welnus the construction that began at the begin of the 2nd Solar war for the day when everything was ready. The project that began all those years ago and had consumed so much of the nations resources. A project that saw the nations brightest minds work tirelessly to complete their goal, harnessing the power of the sun. Experimental reactors had been built all over running constant experiments as the teams learned more and more. They saw many successes and many failures. As the global situation worsened they simply doubled down on their effort.

In March 1986 they would get the breakthrough they had been gunning for throughout the entire project, a breakeven fusion reaction. LET-5 reported breakeven fusion readings, and while the tokamak was able to sustain the reaction for around 60 seconds the plasma eventually destabilized and cooled and the reaction died down. While this was a major milestone the reaction was not what they needed. In order for fusion power to be viable they would have to optimize the reaction to produce around 10 times the input, not to mention the reaction duration would need to be significantly increased. So while a major victory the people working on the project would continue their work.

Over 4 years later the day is here and the reactor constructed deep under the ruins of Welnus had completed its preliminary tests and was now ready to be the first fusion power plant to power a city or well what was left of one anyways. The first ignition outside of tests was to take place at night to get a proper view of the skyline lighting up.

The reactor heat climbed to 100 million Degrees Kelvin, the optimal heat for a Deuterium=Tritium Reaction. The magnetic coils were set to generate the magnetic field that they had spent so much time optimizing to keep the plasma contained...

April 11th, 1991:

Life here for the average Astralian, remote or stubborn to engage with the space projects and clinging onto their home, had changed rapidly; at least here in South Karemi. Between Mutant and Man, both kinds had grown immensely close. In their regular life did they do as much as possible to celebrate and live out their cultures amongst one another, especially the most sentimental parts. No longer was the land rubble, instead it had completely transformed into something similar to a very precise blend of ancient civilization. The critical infrastructure was crude like so, having been rebuilt from the ground-up. Yet, each building that was erected in the place of disaster, whether but a hut or a monastery, heavily derived itself from the most practical of elden technique and architecture, shared between themselves. Houses were being built out of brick or even stone, and on average looked as a confused mix of Kiraidan, Nusian, Rokkanite, Incahindan, Colandian and all the sorts, all at once. Nearly always, such looked over massive fields of slash-and-burn crop fields and other necessary things to be harvested for subsistence.

The population, heavily bottlenecked, sought to merge with eachother to an immense extent for their own survival. There were no borders as we knew them before the Second Solar War. Instead, the population had become so strewn apart yet increasingly attempted to consolidate with those nearest. Thus came the rise of great city-states from the scraps and rubble of the world; usually seated in the former capitals of the former South Karemian nations. The land inbetween, however remained wild and untamed; wandered only by traders, militias and specialists. Life had become all too simple here in Astralis now, centuries removed from what it was before. There is too little left to fight over.
